                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Just hit 65, have 12 AAs to my name, and my gear, while nothing to sneeze at, ain't elemental by a long shot.  I've been charming in LDoN (normal) since I hit 64, and loving it.  My problem is, I just can't last against a charmed mob that's dual-wielding <span style="font-style: italic">and</span> hasted.  AR gets ripped through fast, and unless I'm raid buffed, two interrupts on WoM has me dead.
<br />

<br />
So, what is my best option to balance survivability vs. DPS?  Should I give my pets two weapons, and leave them unhasted, or haste with no weapons?  Or is there a third option to up DPS I'm overlooking?</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=304783" target="_blank" class="postlink">Fallere T`Vala</a>
<br />
Coercer of <a href="http://www.tuatha.cc" target="_blank" class="postlink">Tuatha de Danann</a>
<br />
