                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Get mez mastery before ID5.. I'm absolutely loving MM. Also, of course, channeling helps. I just put 6 points into Channeling3 even before putting the points into TD3..
<br />

<br />
As for haste vs. weapons.. I would imagine that since dual wield doesn't fire every round but haste is an overall increase, the haste will increase DPS more than two weapons. Given that, you would want to max DPS for what you are comfortable with (1. normal mob 2. haste then 3. haste with one weapon 4. haste with two weapons).. I would think that if you had a ranger to steal aggro off you, a paladin offtank who is good at using nondamaging stuns and/or group heals or a druid who spot heals you, you could go all out.. In that sense it depends on the group too.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=361216" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Ariu Vil'Aki</a> <span style="font-size: 9px; line-height: normal">&lt;Heroes&gt;</span><span style="font-size: 9px; line-height: normal">
