                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Starmist: While I am using Uproar, I'm not using RoZ, as I'm not looking to blow a stack of dots every adventure.  I max out CHA with my trophy in the range slot and buffed.  Also, as this is LDoN, my pets are never rootable or snarable.
<br />

<br />
Ariu: That was kind of the logic I had come up with.  But does giving one weapon to a pet produce any more damage than none?
<br />

<br />
Obsin: Mana is rarely an issue for me, so I rarely sit, unless I just had to refresh VoQ and VQ (I miss when my pants were the best clarity I could give, already).  But I hadn't considered a lower-level haste to adjust things.  Great idea!  Ditto on the running into a corner.  I knew that, but it's tough to think about when you've got a pissed pet on you.  I already watch out for interactive objects and such, so I don't WoM too close to them, so watching for a good corner makes sense too.
<br />

<br />
Nadia: Since NDT is a pain to maintain if nobody else in the group wants it, I usually only use it in Rujark, since the puppies can't be shrunk.  Otherwise, the fact that a mob is tiny usually tips the party off.  Also, procs don't have a casting time, so it doesn't really buy you anything there.  I have had a casting mob try to nuke me, only to be protected from it because it was charmed when the nuke went off.  That was pretty amusing.
<br />

<br />
Regane: My typical group is Bard, Warrior, Shaman (healing and slowing, he amazes me sometimes), me and two random DPS, so I rarely have a stunner.  If the bard's really on his toes and he sees me getting beat on, he'll manage to get a mez on my ex-pet, so that's nice.
<br />

<br />
A couple folks mentioned MM, honestly I've never been unable to get a mez or charm off before WoM broke, and all I'm using is SH4.  Mez Mastery really seems like a waste of good AA points to me.  On the other hand, if it really adds a full tick reliably to WoM, I could see the situational advantage to that.
<br />

<br />
As far as the other AAs folks have mentioned, yup, got a big ol' laundry list of wants, though I'm sure most would scoff at my intended order.  I don't really expect to be building them up fast, and the ones I plan on getting first are for the fun factor, so I don't expect to be "uber" any time soon.
<br />

<br />
Thanks for the ideas, and I'd love to hear any more people have for tweaking LDoN charm DPS, without creating a monster I can't control.   <img src="images/smiles/icon_axe.gif" alt="icon_axe.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=304783" target="_blank" class="postlink">Fallere T`Vala</a>
<br />
Coercer of <a href="http://www.tuatha.cc" target="_blank" class="postlink">Tuatha de Danann</a>
