                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I don't know, for me, the trick, anywhere to survive charm breaks has always been distance.
<br />

<br />
The killer, the REAL killer, is the surprise charm break, which is usually the 'multiple instant charm break' thing, that no one is truly ready for.
<br />

<br />
If you stand a good distance away from mobs, you can have time to react to charm breaks and cast mezz from a distance or a pre-emptive morell.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Are you rooting your pet on breaks? If not, target your pet and root as soon as it breaks.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Oh yeah, uhh, charmable LDoN mobs, 100% of them, are immune to root and snare.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
