                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Couple comments on all this..
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Ariu: That was kind of the logic I had come up with. But does giving one weapon to a pet produce any more damage than none? </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
I think this is one of those trial and error things unfortunately. A parser could help you determine, but in some cases it might actually reduce pet DPS  <img src="images/smiles/eusa_think.gif" alt="eusa_think.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
As for NDT duration.. If you get the chance, work on the coldain shawl. You'll find that the 20% extension on all buffs will save you a lot. Also by the time you get SCRM, your buffs will all be 70% extended. My C5 lasts as long as others' C3. My NDT's last 20 mins, meaing I can keep approximately 6 people/pets in Scarecrow form fairly painlessly and 5 is never a problem. NDT is approximately +4 DPS on average (more for high proc'ers who had low DEX, less for those who already had high DEX/attack, etc.. it depends but the average I've parsed is just over 4). NDT is definately worth it on BST MAG and NEC pets as well as a lot of warriors (who tend to proc numerous things).
<br />

<br />
Finally, for charm breaks.. I'm certainly no expert (YET!  <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="icon_biggrin.gif" border="0" />)  but with Mez Mastery and Channeling3 I find that proximity deteremines my ability to wrangle. The only time I ever have trouble is if I WoM too soon when the mob is out of range. Then the spell has to reset and I have to try to root it in the meantime. Because of this I tend to sit only a short distance from the mob so as to get a visual clue when charm breaks and get a 1 sec jump start on WoM, but be within the range of the spell when it casts... WoM resets on interupt so I'd rather have to cast it three times than cast it once OOR.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=361216" target="_blank" class="postlink">Sage Ariu Vil'Aki</a> <span style="font-size: 9px; line-height: normal">&lt;Heroes&gt;</span><span style="font-size: 9px; line-height: normal">
<br />
<a href="http://www.therunes.net/forums/viewtopic.php?p=18979" target="_blank" class="postlink">Enchanter Code v0.2</a>: E65.249/L h- 2.7khp 4.5km ft13(15)@ G++&gt;+++&lt;3 e++&gt;+++ o+ T+++ L+ H++(+++)@ f++ g b-(--) c+++ t+ D++&gt; !X</span></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
