                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Likewise, I only have SH4 but I find that about half the time, my charm lands a split second before WoM wears off and the other half it lands a split second after. As soon as WoM finishes casting, I spam my charm key to start casting it as soon as possible. Blessing of Reverence stacks and helps a lot. Most of the time, I WoM and recharm relying on my channeling skill. If WoM fails, I hit Eldritch and use Bliss to regain control. This is in normal LDONs with no stunner and just a shaman for heals. For reference, the relevant abilities I have are CA1, TD1, and a +8% dodge item. I have no GoD AAs yet and am usually somewhere around 3500hp buffed when I'm in LDON. If I'm in group I trust, I will use SoV to haste my pet. Otherwise, I go with Augmentation.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
