                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Yah, spell haste is very important for that.
<br />

<br />
One of the other keys to making the charm breaks go smoother as well are the defensive AAs... ER, CA/LR, CS/ID, ND.  These AAs will make you a lot more survivable.
<br />

<br />
Corners are also your friend.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">So, what is my best option to balance survivability vs. DPS? Should I give my pets two weapons, and leave them unhasted, or haste with no weapons? Or is there a third option to up DPS I'm overlooking?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Personally, I prefer 2 weapons + unhasted over hasted with no weapons.  Being able to cast WoM between their swings is nice.  Another option that you can use is to not use the max haste.  You do not have to SoV the pet.  You can augment it.  Lasts long, 40% haste.  There's a gap between max haste and no haste.
<br />

<br />
Or at least there was...since reports are that after the patch...no more haste.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
