                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">- hold off on hasting pet until you have seen group in action.  If they (cleric/pally/druid) are covering you, haste that pet.
<br />

<br />
- some chanters carry a stash of ubar charm pet items (haste, hi dmg/prc weaps) they recover once pet no longer useful
<br />

<br />
- wom is your friend and color cloud is a nice cover
<br />

<br />
- a paladin who has the reflex to spot a broken pet and stun is gold
<br />

<br />
- make sure you distinguish ldon from god trials, using wom.cc on a hasted vxed/tipt pet is suicide, using root or asking for snare on a ldon mob is ... futile.
<br />

<br />
- avoid being slower if you plan on charming
<br />

<br />
- remember charm pets have high aggro, if things go south and a load of mobs come send the pet in and then clean up, your pet will tank some - and if it breaks well it was going to either way <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Celenaur Celefeanturi
<br />
"The Silver Ghost"
<br />
ex EMArr, now with Aurora Noctum on The Tribunal.
<br />

<br />
65.105/Tr h- 4khp 5kmp ft5 >+++! !e o++ T+++++ L+ !H f++ g++ b- c++  D- X+++</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
