                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Tend to agree that there really is no need to haste and equip pet.
<br />
I have tried using charm on 2x65 hard adventures now, both times with a slave slayer pet in Rujarkan Hills, and had a lot of fun watching the truly staggering DPS. 
<br />
The tip I would pass on is that 'pet guard here' is your greatest ally for handling charm breaks. I guarded pet about 200 feet behind the current pull spot, and moved his guard spot as we progressed through the dungeon. That seemed to give me (not the fastest of reactions, even on a good day !) time to hit CoD, or WoM, or Bliss as appropriate. Sure, I died once, but the added DPS was worth ten times the res downtime for my group. we finished the adventures faster than the other Hards I have done without charm, was just a little peeved we got no named up on either ;-(</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
